               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/gaussian_stack.png"
               alt="Contact sheet of Gaussian stack levels for the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Gaussian stack (all levels): the apple gradually loses fine grain and edge sharpness as
            the blur level increases, while the overall silhouette and highlight pattern remain
            stable.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/gaussian_level_00.png"
               alt="Fine-scale Gaussian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Gaussian level 0: the original scale retains small speckle, background texture, and a
            crisp boundary between fruit and background.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/gaussian_level_05.png"
               alt="Intermediate Gaussian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Gaussian level 5: mid-level blur suppresses much of the pixel-level noise while keeping
            the stem, specular highlights, and broad shading across the apple’s surface.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/gaussian_level_10.png"
               alt="Coarser Gaussian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Gaussian level 10: only slow intensity variations remain; the object is described mainly
            by its round silhouette and a small number of large highlights and shadows.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/gaussian_level_15.png"
               alt="Very coarse Gaussian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Gaussian level 15: most fine structure has disappeared and the apple is approximated by
            a smooth blob with gentle shading, illustrating the limit of the low-pass hierarchy.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/laplacian_stack.png"
               alt="Contact sheet of Laplacian stack levels for the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Laplacian stack (all levels): each panel encodes detail at a particular scale; fine
            levels emphasize sharp edges and noise, while coarser levels contain broad transitions
            along the fruit’s contour and large highlight regions.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/laplacian_level_00.png"
               alt="Fine-scale Laplacian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Laplacian level 0: highest-frequency band dominated by sensor noise, fabric texture in
            the background, and the thinnest edges around the apple’s boundary.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/laplacian_level_05.png"
               alt="Intermediate Laplacian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Laplacian level 5: mid-frequency band capturing the main contour of the apple and the
            sharper components of the specular highlights, with much of the high-frequency noise
            removed.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/laplacian_level_10.png"
               alt="Coarser Laplacian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Laplacian level 10: coarse band describing broad transitions between the apple and the
            background, as well as large-scale shading variations across the fruit’s body.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="iteration-belt__item">
          <img class="iteration-belt__image"
               src="media/two/3_stacks/apple/laplacian_level_15.png"
               alt="Very coarse Laplacian level of the apple">
          <figcaption class="iteration-belt__caption">
            Laplacian level 15: lowest-frequency band with only very smooth, low-contrast
            structures; the apple appears almost as a ghosted outline, since most energy has shifted
            into coarser Gaussian levels.
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>
    </div>

